description:
I joined Minter Ellison in June 2007.  I specialise in human resources and industrial relations law.  

I have advised on a variety of matters relating to workplace disputes, retention of employees, employee terminations (including allegations of unfair dismissal), employee misconduct matters, industrial disputes, performance management, discrimination, employment related tax, occupational health and safety, electrical safety, the management of injured employees, and the effect of legislation and other industrial instruments. 

I have also assisted in a variety of litigious matters under the Federal and State legislative schemes.

I have a particular interest in industrial strategy, general employment litigation and alternative dispute resolution. My experience in these areas includes:

• Assisting in the strategic resolution of matters, through mediation, conciliation etc, prior to and during the court process including the early resolution of claims involving unfair dismissal, discrimination, contractual claims, workers' compensation etc; 
• The successful defence of the first adverse action case before the Federal Court;
• Successfully bringing actions in relation to alleged industrial action (including applications for orders to stop industrial action, injunctions etc);
• Appearing and advising in relation to urgent applications (same day turnaround);
• Managing complex litigation involving numerous parties and over 40 witnesses.

I advise and represent clients in the health, aged care, mining, construction, energy, education and government sectors. 

Outside of my human resources and industrial relations practice, I am also actively involved in Minter Ellison's Community Investment Program.

In 2011-2012 I completed secondments, as Legal Counsel, to Ergon Energy and Energex.

